<Author>kevmcc
<Content>brilliant! stayed here with my girlfriend in November, we actually booked this hotel based pretty much only on the price, but when we got there couldn't believe how good it was.Less than 5 minutes walk from the Metro station in a quiet part of the city, it looks a bit strange from the outside. Inside is very modern and clean, and all reception staff speak fluent English, which was just as well given that my Spanish extends about as far as asking for beer!The room was actually more like a suite, with a seperate sitting area with a comfortable sofa, a telly and a fairly large dining table. There was also an enclosed balcony area, but there was no way of opening the windows which may be a problem in the summer?We had a problem with the shower on our first morning, which actually turned out to be entirely our fault (we couldn't find the on button) but this was sorted by helpful staff less than 5 minutes after we mentioned it to them.Overall, I would recommend this hotel to anyone. I didn't eat in the restaurant, but it looked good. The whole place was excellent value, I wouldn't have been surprised to pay double what we did! 
