<Content>good value for money considering the hotel is classed as 3* it is fantastic, the rooms are very clean and very spacious. i stayed in a quad room with 3 friends, there was a bedroom with a double bed and in the main living area there were two very comfy sofa beds. there were 2 bathrooms and a balcony.The hotel breakfast was continental that was not really to my taste but others may enjoy this.The hotel receptionist was very friendly and booked us our taxis whenever we required them.....The hotel was very reasonably priced it cost 40 euros each, beware of the %7 tax charge on arrival though, as this was not mentioned when booked. 
